The paper discusses the performance of DAG-based protocols for cryptocurrencies, which involves topics related to cryptography (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), networking (cs.NI), data structures (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on the fairness and efficiency of these protocols, which suggests a stronger emphasis on distributed computing and data structures, but the involvement of networking and social and information networks cannot be ignored.
